HEADWORD: off-peak
<hw>off-peak</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Having less than maximal use or
demand or activity; -- of a period of time occurring as a defined part
of a time cycle; <as>as, <ex>off-peak</ex> telephone rates are available
at night and on weekends; <ex>off-peak</ex> fares</as>.</def> [Narrower
terms: <stype>off-season </stype>] <ant>peak</ant>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

